(1, '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sakela&lt;/strong&gt;, also known as&nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Sakewa&lt;/strong&gt;&nbsp;or&nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Sakenwa&lt;/strong&gt;&nbsp;(&lt;a title=&quot;Nepali language&quot; href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nepali_language&quot;&gt;Nepali&lt;/a&gt;:&nbsp;&lt;span lang=&quot;ne&quot;&gt;साकेला&lt;/span&gt;), is one of the main festivals of the&nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Rai people&quot; href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rai_people&quot;&gt;Khambu&lt;/a&gt;&nbsp;(Rai people), an ethnic group indigenous to Eastern&nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Nepal&quot; href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nepal&quot;&gt;Nepal&lt;/a&gt;&nbsp;and the&nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Sikkim&quot; href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sikkim&quot;&gt;Sikkim&lt;/a&gt;,&nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Kalimpong&quot; href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kalimpong&quot;&gt;Kalimpong&lt;/a&gt;, and&nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;Darjeeling&quot; href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Darjeeling&quot;&gt;Darjeeling&lt;/a&gt;&nbsp;regions of&nbsp;&lt;a title=&quot;India&quot; href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India&quot;&gt;India&lt;/a&gt;. Sakela is celebrated twice a year and is distinguished by two names:&nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Ubhauli&quot; href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ubhauli&quot;&gt;Ubhauli&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&nbsp;and&nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Udhauli&quot; href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Udhauli&quot;&gt;Udhauli&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;. Sakela&nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Ubhauli&lt;/em&gt;&nbsp;is celebrated during&nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;mw-redirect&quot; title=&quot;Baisakh Purnima&quot; href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baisakh_Purnima&quot;&gt;Baisakh Purnima&lt;/a&gt;&nbsp;(the full moon day in the month of&nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;mw-redirect&quot; title=&quot;Baishakh (Nepali calendar)&quot; href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baishakh_(Nepali_calendar)&quot;&gt;Baisakh&lt;/a&gt;) and Sakela&nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Udhauli&lt;/em&gt;&nbsp;is celebrated during the full moon day in the month of&nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;mw-redirect&quot; title=&quot;Mangsir (Nepali calendar)&quot; href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mangsir_(Nepali_calendar)&quot;&gt;Mangsir&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;sup id=&quot;cite_ref-gaenszle1997changing_1-0&quot; class=&quot;reference&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sakela#cite_note-gaenszle1997changing-1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;cite-bracket&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;1&lt;span class=&quot;cite-bracket&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sup id=&quot;cite_ref-schlemmer2004new_2-0&quot; class=&quot;reference&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sakela#cite_note-schlemmer2004new-2&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;cite-bracket&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;2&lt;span class=&quot;cite-bracket&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sup id=&quot;cite_ref-kathmandupost2011_3-0&quot; class=&quot;reference&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sakela#cite_note-kathmandupost2011-3&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;cite-bracket&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;3&lt;span class=&quot;cite-bracket&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '', '', '', '1');
